components.contentUniquenessFloor: Lowest pairwise rendered-text uniqueness score for the page.
components.keywordOwnership: Share of page keyword phrases that are not reused by other generated URLs.
components.signalIsolation: 1 - maximum synthetic uniqueness-signal overlap against any other page.
components.urlPatternCompliance: 1 when URL matches clean static family pattern (/format/* or /compare/*) with no query/hash.

strategy: One primary keyword per URL path.
Self-referencing canonical on every pSEO page.
No query-string indexable pages; only folder-based slugs.
Rendered text similarity checks (cosine + Jaccard) run on generated page bodies.
Synthetic uniqueness signals remain as a secondary overlap guardrail.
Meaningful uniqueness strategy score blends raw text uniqueness with keyword ownership, signal isolation, and static URL-pattern compliance.
